features =['danceability','energy','key','loudness', 'mode', 
           'speechiness', 'acousticness', 'instrumentalness', 
           'liveness','valence','tempo','duration_ms', 'time_signature']

x = spotify.loc[:,features].values
x = StandardScaler().fit_transform(x)

Principal Component Analysis¶

In [4]:
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
principal_components = pca.fit_transform(x)

principal_df = pd.DataFrame(data=principal_components, columns=['principal_component_1', 'principal_component_2'])

music_data_pca = principal_df.to_numpy()
kmeans_pca = KMeans(n_clusters=8, random_state=0, init='random').fit(music_data_pca)
predicted_pca = kmeans_pca.fit_predict(music_data_pca)
target_df_pca = principal_df.copy()
target_df_pca['prediction'] = predicted_pca
target_df_pca.set_index(keys=spotify.index, inplace=True)
target_df_pca.head()

t-SNE¶

In [7]:
tsne = TSNE(n_components=2)
x_embedded = tsne.fit_transform(x)
x_tsne = x_embedded[:,0]
y_tsne = x_embedded[:,1]
tsne_df = pd.DataFrame(data={'tsne_1': x_tsne,'tsne_2': y_tsne})

music_data_tsne = tsne_df.to_numpy()
kmeans_tsne = KMeans(n_clusters=8, random_state=0, init='random').fit(music_data_tsne)
predicted_tsne = kmeans_tsne.fit_predict(music_data_tsne)

target_df_tsne = tsne_df.copy()
target_df_tsne['prediction'] = predicted_tsne
target_df_tsne.set_index(keys=spotify.index, inplace=True)

In [71]:
def plot_feature(df,feature):
    """Plots the distribution of a given audio feature across a group of tracks"""
    sns.distplot(df[feature])
    plt.xlabel('{}'.format(feature), fontsize=18)
    plt.grid(True)
    
def plot_analysis(df):
    """Creates a 12 element plot that visualizes all audio features for a group of tracks"""
    features = list(df.columns[1:12]) + list(df.columns[-1:])
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
    for (i, feature) in zip(range(1,13),features):
        plt.subplot(4,3,i)
        plot_feature(feature) 
    plt.suptitle('Visual Analysis of Spotify Top Songs')
    plt.tight_layout()
    
def compare(df1, df2):
    """Overlays the audio analysis of two groups of tracks to easier compare differences"""
    features = list(df1.columns[1:12]) + ['duration_ms']
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
    for (i,feature) in zip(range(1,13), features):
        plt.subplot(4,3,i)
        plot_feature(df1, feature) 
        plot_feature(df2, feature)
    #plt.suptitle('Comparison of Classical and Pop', fontsize=25)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig('classical_vs_pop2.png', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=450)
